Mauritius Plans to Build 2.7-Kilometer Bridge, Le Matinal Says

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-03-30T06:26:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/mauritius-plans-to-build-2-7-kilometer-bridge-le-matinal-says.html
Mauritius plans to build a 2.7-
kilometer (1.7-mile) bridge over the  Port Louis  harbor, Le
Matinal said, citing an unnamed officer at the Road Development
Authority.  The bridge will be built through a public-private
partnership, the Port Louis-based newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in Port Louis via Johannesburg at 
1933 or  gbell16@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at   asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 